# College Management System

This is a console-based College Management System implemented in C#. The system allows users to manage students, professors, and class enrollments within a college.

## Features

- Add new students and professors to the system.
- Enroll students in classes.
- View all students and professors.
- View students enrolled in a specific class.

## Getting Started

To run the College Management System, follow these steps:

1. Ensure you have the .NET SDK installed on your machine. You can download it from [here](https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download).
2. Clone this repository to your local machine.
3. Navigate to the project directory using the command line.
4. Compile the code using the following command:

    ```
    dotnet build
    ```

5. Run the application using the following command:

    ```
    dotnet run
    ```

## Usage

Upon running the application, you will be presented with a menu-driven interface. You can choose options to add students, add professors, enroll students in classes, view all students, view all professors, view students in a class, or exit the program.